datasets.name: a5510c39
queryLines:
use catalog identifier(:catalog);

use schema identifier(:schema);

select
  case
    when dashboard_name rlike '.* [0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2} .*' then 'unnamed_dashboard'
    else dashboard_name
  end as dashboard_name,
  sum(num_views) as num_views
from
  mvFactDashboardUsage
  where viewed_date >= now()-interval 14 days
  group by dashboard_name
  having
  num_views < 10

datasets.name: 9d2c306d
queryLines:
use catalog identifier(:catalog);

use schema identifier(:schema);

WITH weekly_views AS (
  SELECT
    dashboard_id,
    workspace_id,
    first(dashboard_name) as dashboard_name,
    weekofyear(viewed_date) AS week_num,
    COUNT(*) AS num_views
  FROM mvFactDashboardUsage
  WHERE viewed_date >= current_date() - INTERVAL 21 DAYS
  GROUP BY dashboard_id, workspace_id, weekofyear(viewed_date)
),
weekly_ranks AS (
  SELECT
    dashboard_id,
    workspace_id,
    dashboard_name,
    week_num,
    num_views,
    DENSE_RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY week_num ORDER BY num_views DESC) AS week_rank
  FROM weekly_views
),
pivoted AS (
  SELECT
    dashboard_id,
    workspace_id,
    first(dashboard_name) as dashboard_name,
    MAX(CASE WHEN week_num = weekofyear(current_date()) THEN num_views END) AS week_0_views,
    MAX(CASE WHEN week_num = weekofyear(current_date() - INTERVAL 7 DAYS) THEN num_views END) AS week_1_views,
    MAX(CASE WHEN week_num = weekofyear(current_date() - INTERVAL 14 DAYS) THEN num_views END) AS week_2_views,
    MAX(CASE WHEN week_num = weekofyear(current_date()) THEN week_rank END) AS week_0_rank,
    MAX(CASE WHEN week_num = weekofyear(current_date() - INTERVAL 7 DAYS) THEN week_rank END) AS week_1_rank,
    MAX(CASE WHEN week_num = weekofyear(current_date() - INTERVAL 14 DAYS) THEN week_rank END) AS week_2_rank,
    SUM(num_views) AS total_views
  FROM weekly_ranks
  GROUP BY dashboard_id,workspace_id
),
ranked AS (
  SELECT
    dashboard_id,
    workspace_id,
    dashboard_name,
    week_0_views,
    week_1_views,
    week_2_views,
    week_0_rank,
    week_1_rank,
    week_2_rank,
    total_views,
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY total_views DESC) AS overall_rank
  FROM pivoted
)
SELECT
  overall_rank,
  r.dashboard_name,
  dashboard_id,
  workspace_id,
  coalesce(week_0_views,week_1_views) AS this_week_views,
  coalesce(week_0_rank,week_1_rank) AS this_week_rank,
  week_1_views AS last_week_views,
  week_1_rank AS last_week_rank,
  week_2_views AS two_weeks_ago_views,
  week_2_rank AS two_weeks_ago_rank,
  this_week_rank - last_week_rank AS rank_change,
  concat(:your_workspace_url, '/dashboardsv3/', :dashboard_id,'/published?o=', workspace_id, '&f_f4350a1a%7Edashboard=',dashboard_id) as drillthrough_url
FROM ranked r
WHERE overall_rank <= 10
ORDER BY overall_rank
--

use catalog identifier(:catalog);

use schema identifier(:schema);
with ranked as (
SELECT
  genie_space,
  SUM(num_views) AS total_views,
  SUM(num_chats_created) AS total_chats,
  RANK() OVER (ORDER BY SUM(num_views) DESC) AS views_rank,
  RANK() OVER (ORDER BY SUM(num_chats_created) DESC) AS chats_rank
FROM
  mvFactGenieUsage
GROUP BY
  genie_space
)
select genie_space, total_views, total_chats, views_rank, chats_rank from ranked where views_rank <= 10 or chats_rank <=10

datasets.name: dcb76dbb
queryLines:
select
  regexp_replace(user_identity.email, r'^[^.]+(?=\.)', "*****") as username,
  count(user_identity) as total_dashboard_clicks
from
  system.access.audit
where
  action_name = 'getDashboard'
  and event_time >= current_timestamp() - interval 7 days
  and response.status_code = 200
group by
  user_identity.email
having
  total_dashboard_clicks > 10
order by
  total_dashboard_clicks desc
  limit 10;

datasets.name: 26e7cfc1
queryLines:
use catalog identifier(:catalog);

use schema identifier(:schema);
with ranked as (
SELECT
  genie_space,
  SUM(num_views) AS total_views,
  SUM(num_chats_created) AS total_chats,
  RANK() OVER (ORDER BY SUM(num_views) DESC) AS views_rank,
  RANK() OVER (ORDER BY SUM(num_chats_created) DESC) AS chats_rank
FROM
  mvFactGenieUsage
GROUP BY
  genie_space
)
select 'most_viewed' as status, * from ranked where views_rank = 1
union all
select 'least_viewed' as status, * from ranked where views_rank = (select max(views_rank) from ranked) limit 2

  count(user_identity) as total_genie_interactions

  system.access.audit

  lower(action_name) ilike '%genie%'

 FROM   system.access.audit

and request_params["client_id"] != 'databricks-cli'
and response.status_code = 200
group by all

queryLines:
SELECT
  event_date,
  workspace_id,
  request_params['request_object_id'] as app,
  user_identity['email'] as sharing_user,
  acl_entry['group_name'],
  acl_entry['user_name'],
  acl_entry['permission_level']
FROM
  system.access.audit t
LATERAL VIEW
  explode(from_json(request_params['access_control_list'], 'array<struct<user_name:string,permission_level:string,group_name:string>>')) acl_entry AS acl_entry
WHERE
  action_name = 'changeAppsAcl'
AND
  request_params['request_object_type'] = 'apps'
ORDER BY
  event_date DESC

datasets.name: f8608a63
queryLines:
use catalog identifier(:catalog);

use schema identifier(:schema);

WITH monthly_views AS (
  SELECT
    dashboard_id,
    any_value(dashboard_name) as dashboard_name,
    DATE_TRUNC('month', viewed_date) AS month,
    SUM(num_views) AS total_views
  FROM mvFactDashboardUsage
  WHERE viewed_date >= DATE_TRUNC('month', CURRENT_DATE) - INTERVAL '1' MONTH
  GROUP BY dashboard_id, DATE_TRUNC('month', viewed_date)
),
pivoted AS (
  SELECT
    dashboard_name,
    MAX(CASE WHEN month = DATE_TRUNC('month', CURRENT_DATE) THEN total_views END) AS this_month_views,
    MAX(CASE WHEN month = DATE_TRUNC('month', CURRENT_DATE) - INTERVAL '1' MONTH THEN total_views END) AS last_month_views
  FROM monthly_views
  GROUP BY dashboard_name
),
diffs AS (
  SELECT
    dashboard_name,
    COALESCE(this_month_views, 0) - COALESCE(last_month_views, 0) AS view_diff
  FROM pivoted
),
climbers AS (
  SELECT
    dashboard_name,
    view_diff,
    'Climber' AS type,
    1 AS sort_order,
    DENSE_RANK() OVER (ORDER BY view_diff DESC) AS rank
  FROM diffs
  ORDER BY view_diff DESC
  LIMIT 20
),
decliners AS (
  SELECT
    dashboard_name,
    view_diff,
    'Decliner' AS type,
    2 AS sort_order,
    DENSE_RANK() OVER (ORDER BY view_diff ASC) AS rank
  FROM diffs
  ORDER BY view_diff ASC
  LIMIT 20
)
SELECT dashboard_name, view_diff, type, rank
FROM (
  (SELECT dashboard_name, view_diff, type, sort_order, rank FROM climbers)
  UNION ALL
  (SELECT dashboard_name, view_diff, type, sort_order, rank FROM decliners)
)
ORDER BY sort_order, rank
